edu.wit.dcsn.comp2000.listadt

Interface ListInterface<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - the class (or an ancestor class) of objects to be stored in the list
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    LinkedListPlus

    public interface ListInterface<T>
    An interface for the ADT List. Entries in the list have positions that begin with 0.

    Revised: 2018-07-11 by David M Rosenberg
    Revised: 2017-07-05 by David M Rosenberg
    Revised: 2016-11-08 by David M Rosenberg

    • Method Detail

      • add

        void add(T newEntry)
        Task: Adds a new entry to the end of the list. Entries currently in the list are unaffected. The list's size is increased by 1.
        Parameters:
        newEntry - the object to be added as a new entry

      • add

        void add(int newPosition,
         T newEntry)
        Task: Adds a new entry at a specified position within the list. Entries originally at and above the specified position move to the next higher position within the list. The list's size is increased by 1.
        Parameters:
        newPosition - an integer that specifies the desired position of the new entry
        newEntry - the object to be added as a new entry

      • clear

        void clear()
        Task: Removes all entries from the list.

      • remove

        T remove(int givenPosition)
        Task: Removes the entry at a given position from the list. Entries originally at positions higher than the given position move to the next lower position within the list, and the list's size is decreased by 1.
        Parameters:
        givenPosition - an integer that indicates the position of the entry to be removed
        Returns:
        if successful, a reference to the removed entry, otherwise null (e.g. givenPosition < 0, or givenPosition ≥ getLength()

      • replace

        T replace(int givenPosition,
          T newEntry)
        Task: Replaces the entry at a given position in the list.
        Parameters:
        givenPosition - an integer that indicates the position of the entry to be replaced
        newEntry - the object that will replace the entry at the position givenPosition
        Returns:
        a reference to the replaced entry if the replacement is successful, otherwise null (e.g. givenPosition < 0, givenPosition > getLength(), or newEntry isn't valid/acceptable)

      • getEntry

        T getEntry(int givenPosition)
        Task: Retrieves the entry at a given position in the list.
        Parameters:
        givenPosition - an integer that indicates the position of the desired entry
        Returns:
        if successful, a reference to the indicated entry, otherwise null (e.g. givenPosition < 0 or givenPosition > getLength())

      • contains

        boolean contains(T anEntry)
        Task: Sees whether the list contains a given entry.
        Parameters:
        anEntry - the object that is the desired entry
        Returns:
        true if the list contains anEntry, or false if not

      • getLength

        int getLength()
        Task: Gets the length of the list.
        Returns:
        the integer number of entries currently in the list

      • isEmpty

        boolean isEmpty()
        Task: Sees whether the list is empty.
        Returns:
        true if the list is empty, or false if not
